  "text": "This article makes two main contributions. First, it helps to advance present discussion at the intersection between marketing and entrepreneurship. As most studies of these two fields are of a more general nature [CITATION_1] , this research focuses on activities specifically carried out during the firm's initial period of life. Second, this article enhances knowledge in the field by showing that not only is it vital to engage in marketing activities, as the literature has already shown, but also by showing at what moment these marketing activities generate greatest impact. The research considers that the entrepreneur undertakes different activities in the first and second years of the business and, by making different combinations from the beginning of these activities, this study presents the ideal moment for carrying out each marketing activity. This research which is of a longitudinal nature, used data from the Panel Study of Entrepreneurial Dynamics II (PSED II).",
